cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

The paper proposes a model for disentangling appearance and geometric information from images, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The model is trained in an unsupervised manner, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model also involves geometric warping, which is related to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
